Subject: [PATCH 3/5] feat: positional keep-one track removal for dedup
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add remove_specific_track_occurrences, exposing spotipy's
playlist_remove_specific_occurrences_of_items so callers can delete
individual copies of a track by 0-based position instead of every
occurrence of a URI — the operation needed to deduplicate a playlist
while keeping one copy.

Route both removal tools through a shared _confirm_removal helper so the
new positional path uses the exact same destructive-elicitation gate as
remove_tracks_from_playlist.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
